00:03:29.470 --> 00:03:31.359
Let's talk about some must knows.

00:03:31.750 --> 00:03:33.579
First, the RBI's role.

00:03:34.089 --> 00:03:37.989
The Reserve Bank of India is our
country's central bank, the big boss.

00:03:38.625 --> 00:03:44.144
It's responsible for monetary policy
regulating banks and issuing our currency.

00:03:44.655 --> 00:03:48.975
We have different types of banks, like
commercial banks, which include public

00:03:48.975 --> 00:03:53.804
sector, private sector, and foreign
banks, as well as cooperative banks,

00:03:54.015 --> 00:03:56.565
payments banks, and small finance banks.

00:03:56.984 --> 00:03:59.535
You must also know the key policy rates.

00:03:59.924 --> 00:04:03.494
The repo rate is the rate
at which RBI lends to banks.

00:04:03.920 --> 00:04:05.870
The reverse report rate is the opposite.

00:04:06.230 --> 00:04:12.980
The rate at which RBI borrows from banks,
then their CRR or cash reserve ratio,

00:04:13.220 --> 00:04:16.640
and SLR, the statutory liquidity ratio.

00:04:17.120 --> 00:04:21.290
When it comes to financial instruments,
you have everything from your basic

00:04:21.290 --> 00:04:26.090
savings and current accounts, fixed
and recurring deposits to loans, mutual

00:04:26.090 --> 00:04:28.940
funds, shares, bonds, and insurance.

00:04:29.335 --> 00:04:32.815
And who keeps everyone in
line, the regulatory bodies.

00:04:33.205 --> 00:04:37.555
The RBI looks after banks, sebi
handles the capital markets.

00:04:37.705 --> 00:04:40.135
I-R-D-A-I manages insurance.

00:04:40.255 --> 00:04:42.805
And P-F-R-D-A is for pension funds.

00:04:43.255 --> 00:04:48.745
A very important concept is financial
inclusion, which means making financial

00:04:48.745 --> 00:04:52.765
services available to people who
don't have them through things like

00:04:52.765 --> 00:04:56.784
no frills accounts, mobile banking,
and direct benefit transfers.

00:04:58.049 --> 00:04:59.340
Methods of solving.

00:04:59.820 --> 00:05:02.039
When you see a question, don't panic.

00:05:02.219 --> 00:05:04.380
Use these methods first.

00:05:04.530 --> 00:05:06.059
Keyword identification.

00:05:06.419 --> 00:05:11.219
Read the question carefully and spot
the main financial term or institution.

00:05:11.489 --> 00:05:12.900
This helps you focus.

00:05:13.260 --> 00:05:15.419
Then do some option analysis.

00:05:15.809 --> 00:05:20.580
Look at each option and see how well it
fits with the keyword you identified.

00:05:21.010 --> 00:05:23.469
The elimination method
is your best friend.

00:05:23.469 --> 00:05:26.979
When you're stuck, start by
throwing out the options that are

00:05:27.010 --> 00:05:29.380
obviously wrong or don't make sense.

00:05:29.739 --> 00:05:33.580
This seriously increases your
chances for trickier questions.

00:05:33.669 --> 00:05:35.320
Use contextual reasoning.

00:05:35.679 --> 00:05:39.190
Think about how these financial
ideas work in the real world

00:05:39.340 --> 00:05:40.989
to figure out the best answer.

00:05:41.320 --> 00:05:46.270
And of course, sometimes you just have
to rely on recall of facts directly

00:05:46.270 --> 00:05:48.729
remembering the definitions and details.

00:05:49.500 --> 00:05:53.729
Shortcuts and smart techniques
want to be a little clever.

00:05:54.090 --> 00:05:57.719
Use acronym association for abbreviations.

00:05:57.900 --> 00:06:05.130
Link the first letter to a related word,
for example, F in IFSC is for financial.

00:06:05.130 --> 00:06:05.370
Easy peasy.

00:06:06.695 --> 00:06:11.945
Also try categorization mentally
group things like investment

00:06:11.945 --> 00:06:15.695
products or regulators to
recall their features quickly.

00:06:16.265 --> 00:06:21.935
The odd one out strategy works wonders
if a question asks for an exception,

00:06:22.145 --> 00:06:26.044
scan the options for the one that
doesn't belong with the others.

00:06:26.554 --> 00:06:29.200
A great technique is
current affairs linkage.

00:06:29.840 --> 00:06:31.340
Many static questions.

00:06:31.400 --> 00:06:32.599
Have a current angle.

00:06:33.020 --> 00:06:37.280
Connect the concept to any recent
news you've read, and finally

00:06:37.430 --> 00:06:39.289
focus on the core function.

